steps.step: Process arugula, basil, oil, parmesan, pine nuts, lemon zest, garlic and salt in a food processor or blender until finely chopped; season with pepper, to taste.
Serve immediately or store in the refrigerator covered with a thin layer of olive oil for up to three days, or in the freezer for up to three months.

results.title: Easy zucchini and chicken breast casserole

steps.step: Slice the chicken breast fillets into thin slices. Season them with salt, black pepper and paprika as taste. Rub the slices with crushed garlic.Crack the eggs into a deep bowl and beat them with a fork. Season with a pinch of salt.Prepare an ovenproof dish for the casserole: grease the dish with 2 tablespoon oil.Preheat the oven to 160C / 320F.Dip the chicken breast slices in the beaten eggs, then coat the slices in the grated cheese. Line the chicken slices in the ovenproof dish.
Cut the zucchinis into 1 cm / 0,4 inches. Line the zucchini slices on top of the chicken breasts.
Mix the rest of the beaten eggs with the singe cream.
Pour the mixture on top of the zucchini.
Sprinkle the top of the casserole with the leftover cheese.
Place the casserole in the preheated oven and bake it for 25 minutes until the top is golden brown.
